In England, in the seven days to 11 September, there were 168,049 new confirmed cases (297.2 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 04 September, there were 187,599 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 10% (19,550 fewer cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 16 September is 6,281,236 (11,107.4 cases per 100,000 population).
